<concept id="concept_f4y_spy_dw">
 <title>Cache</title>
 <shortdesc>The Hive Metastore destination queries Hive for information and caches the results. When
        possible, it uses the cache to avoid unnecessary Hive queries.</shortdesc>
 <conbody>
  <p><indexterm>Hive Metastore
                    destination<indexterm>cache</indexterm></indexterm><indexterm>cache<indexterm>for
                    the Hive Metastore destination</indexterm></indexterm>The destination caches the
            following Hive metadata:<ul id="ul_y1l_2dt_dw">
                <li>Database and table to be written to</li>
                <li>Hive table properties</li>
                <li>Column names and types in the table</li>
                <li>Partition values</li>
            </ul></p>
 </conbody>
</concept>
